## 4. Library Quick-Reference

| Need | Library | Install | Speed |
|------|---------|---------|-------|
| Classical graph algorithms | `networkx` | `pip install networkx` | Medium |
| Fast classical algorithms | `igraph` (Python bindings) | `pip install igraph` | Fast (C backend) |
| Louvain community detection | `python-louvain` | `pip install python-louvain` | Medium |
| Leiden (better than Louvain) | `leidenalg` | `pip install leidenalg` | Fast |
| node2vec embeddings | `node2vec` | `pip install node2vec` | Medium |
| GNN training | `torch_geometric` (PyG) | See PyG install guide | GPU-accelerated |
| GNN alternative | `dgl` | `pip install dgl` | GPU-accelerated |
| High-level GNN API | `stellargraph` | `pip install stellargraph` | Medium |
| Misc. embeddings | `karateclub` | `pip install karateclub` | Medium |
| Graph visualisation | `gephi` / `pyvis` | `pip install pyvis` | — |

---

## 5. When to Use What

| Situation | Recommendation |
|-----------|---------------|
| Small graph (<100K nodes), need exact results | NetworkX |
| Large graph (>1M nodes), need speed | igraph |
| Need node embeddings for downstream ML | node2vec (karateclub) or PyG Node2Vec |
| Node classification with features | GCN / GraphSAGE (PyG) |
| Link prediction | PyG + custom edge features |
| Community detection, production | Leiden (leidenalg) |
| Streaming / incremental graph updates | Custom incremental PageRank |
| GDS available in Neo4j | Use GDS — it's faster and stays in-database |

